⠀ 
⠀ 
This video felt super necessary, because the fact that I now have 3 coffee machines is absolutely absurd BUT also makes a lot of sense..
⠀ 
I had a few specific requirements when looking for a coffee machine:
⠀ 
1: BPA-free (b/c if there's something i'm going to consume daily or regularly, I would prefer that it's not heated in plastic. Plastic is already not great for you on it's own, but it's another thing when you heat it as this can release more of it into your food/drinks)
⠀ 
2: Wanted an automatic grinder so I could buy fresh organic beans, but not deal with such an ordeal everyday of grinding them separately.
⠀ 
3: I wanted to be able to make coffee AND espresso, because sometimes I want a latte, and sometimes I want coffee 💁🏻‍♀️ (i also wanted the option of offering both to guests when they come over)
⠀ 
Also - I bought and returned 2 machines .. because they say stainless steel, then when they arrive they're part plastic part stainless steel. I'M EXHAUSTED WRITING THIS CAPTION so imagine how I felt in the process haha.
⠀ 
ANYWAY - These 3 are the best ones I found, and when it comes to coffee, I buy organic medium roast beans (@allegrocoffee is great, and they offer a swiss water decaf version!). When it comes to pods I like @artizancoffeecompany because they're organic, have Swiss water decaf options, and decomposable! SUCH a good find... and they're compatible with a lot of nespresso machines).
⠀ 
If you want more details on this in a blog post with links leave a ☕️

Some updates:
⠀ 
Farsi is going so well… my mom and dad were both SHOCKED at how well i can read. They didn’t see it coming 😉 i might not know everything I’m reading yet lol, but my teacher told me learning to read and write really helps you learn to speak a language as an adult. This is different than learning as a kid. Also shoutout to all the amazing suggestions you guys commented and dm’d me with .. that’s how i found her and she’s incredible! (She doesn’t have Instagram and I’m not sure if she wants me to share her info)…
⠀
I’ve really been slowing down. It’s an adjustment… I’m used to being go go go. I used to always say my career is what gave me my self confidence. And I’ve since learned that no external factors are truly responsible for how you feel about yourself. It’s just a mask, and it’s incredibly unstable because you can’t control the outside. So any inevitable shift will alter how you feel inside. Which is exactly what I’ve experienced in the past. So… we’re diving in deep over here 💜 also working on shifting the projects i focus on from ego/self-fulfillment to true inspiration. It seems like such a small adjustment but it’s so real!
⠀ 
Spending a lot of time with family this summer which i love
⠀ 
AND - I’m so excited for a few projects coming up, especially a new series i want to film soon. The more I honor this moment in my life and take a pause the more right these few things feel…
⠀ 
*Cover up from @fwrd @melissasimoneswim sandals @ganni sunglasses @celine

Fruit and coffee in the morning just do it for me. I like to ask for the fruit to come right away, have it as an appetizer so i can digest it a bit, then move on to whatever I’m having for breakfast
⠀ 
Fruit on its own / on an empty stomach / in the morning is something I’ve been doing for a few years. Of course I’m not a full stickler but i usually feel best doing it this way. I originally learned about this food combining principle from @_kimberlysnyder’s first book. But i continue to see other naturopathic doctors and Ayurvedic doctors believe in and follow this principle. On the other hand, many other food principles don’t believe in it at all. Lots of different opinions
⠀ 
I’m not here to say it’s right or wrong, i think it’s naive to believe that your way is the 100% right and only way. I’m just here to share my personal experience.. and I personally love it 🙌🏼🤍
⠀ 
Does anyone else feel better or notice a difference eating this way?

node.text:
Last night I was having dinner with one of my best friends from pharmacy school who I haven’t seen in a while, and she was like “so what do you actually do??” (😆). So I proceeded to explain to her the ins and outs of content creation, outlining pages of prep for the educational YouTube videos I put out, the process of working with brands and the back and forth on content previews and approval, writing blogs, affiliate partnerships, keeping up with mostly organic content, etc. And I had one of those moments where I couldn’t believe how far I’ve come since my days at the pharmacy and how I was actually able to make this a successful career, not just a hobby.
⠀ 
So I just wanted to say thank you to everyone in this community who has followed my journey and supported me 🤍 I ran into two of you last night (thank u for saying hi) and it was just really rewarding to hear how much you appreciate my content and the way it’s helped you ❤️🥲
⠀ 
I’m not quite sure what’s next for me, but whatever it is I will strive to make sure I’m thinking of you and that it brings you the most value. I want to make that move when I’m absolutely positive it’s the right thing, similar to how I felt when i started pursuing content creation ❤️
⠀ 
PS - Outfit is @charoruizibiza. I loveeee this set

Things I value: true connections, friendships that warm the soul, quality time, being good to myself in all forms of mental and physical well-being, LOVE, family, passion. Grateful for this special bond with my @melissawoodhealth. We met through Insta (3 1/2? 4? years ago. I can’t remember now) and our fate is lifelong friendship... calling it☺️💗
⠀ 
Btw - didn’t get the full experience of float tank bc we went in together and were laughing the whole time (we needed a catch up lol) but excited to try this amazing wellness practice another time. It’s been shown to help with anxiety, pain, stress and more.
⠀ 
Ate at @serafinanewyork after - the veggie salad with lemon dressing is more delicious than i can explain 😆 so is the pasta
⠀ 
My set is by @nicholasthelabel
